{# templates/roadmaps/real-state/hidden-costs.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('real_state_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('real_state_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- Article Hero -->
        <div class="article-hero animate" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2f2a24 0%, #5e4b3f 100%);">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">
                    <i class="fas fa-wrench"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>The Hidden Costs of Homeownership <span>Taxes, Insurance, Maintenance</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    The purchase price is just the beginning. Property taxes, homeowners insurance, and ongoing maintenance can add thousands to your annual budget. Learn what to expect and how to plan.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag" style="background-color: rgba(225,112,85,0.2); color: #f7b9a9;">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 2: Risk Management · 7 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">💰 The Real Price of a Roof Over Your Head</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                When you rent, your landlord handles the surprises. When you own, every leaky faucet, property tax bill, and insurance premium is yours to pay.
                <strong>Understanding these costs before you buy</strong> can mean the difference between a comfortable investment and a financial strain.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- The Big Three (using rule-grid) -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-landmark"></i> Property Taxes</h4>
                <p>Annual tax paid to local government, typically 0.5–2.5% of the home's assessed value. Can increase over time. Often escrowed into your mortgage payment.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-shield"></i> Homeowners Insurance</h4>
                <p>Protects against fire, theft, liability, and more. Average cost: $1,200–$2,500/year depending on location, coverage, and home value.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Maintenance & Repairs</h4>
                <p>The 1% rule: set aside at least 1% of your home's value each year for upkeep. A $300,000 home = $3,000/year. Big-ticket items (roof, HVAC) come every 15–20 years.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Deep Dive Card -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-magnifying-glass-dollar"></i> Why These Costs Matter</h3>
            <p>Many first‑time buyers focus only on the mortgage payment and forget that <strong>PITI (Principal, Interest, Taxes, Insurance)</strong> is just the baseline. Then maintenance hits – and if you're unprepared, you might end up on credit cards.</p>
            <p style="background: var(--light-gray); padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px;">
                <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Before buying, ask the seller for utility bills and any recent repair history. Also check local tax records – some areas reassess after a sale, raising your taxes.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Interactive Tool: Hidden Cost Calculator (disabled for non-logged-in) -->
        <div class="card animate" id="hidden-cost-calculator">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-calculator"></i> Interactive: Total Homeownership Cost Estimator</h3>
            <p>See how property taxes, insurance, and maintenance add up over time.</p>

            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 20px; margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Home Purchase Price ($) <span id="homePriceValHidden">300000</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="homePriceHidden" min="50000" max="1000000" value="300000" step="5000" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Down Payment (%) <span id="downPercentValHidden">20</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="downPercentHidden" min="3" max="50" value="20" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Property Tax Rate (%/year) <span id="taxRateValHidden">1.0</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="taxRateHidden" min="0.5" max="3" value="1.0" step="0.1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Annual Insurance ($) <span id="insuranceValHidden">1500</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="insuranceHidden" min="500" max="5000" value="1500" step="100" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Maintenance (% of value/year) <span id="maintValHidden">1.0</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="maintHidden" min="0.5" max="3" value="1.0" step="0.1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
                <div style="flex: 1 1 200px;">
                    <label>Years to Project <span id="yearsValHidden">5</span></label>
                    <input type="range" id="yearsHidden" min="1" max="30" value="5" step="1" class="cat-input" style="width:100%;">
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="margin-top: 20px;">
                <button id="calcHiddenCosts" class="btn-outline">Calculate Total Cost</button>
            </div>

            <div id="hiddenCostsResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 20px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px;">
                <p>Adjust the values and click the button.</p>
            </div>

            <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px;">
                <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> This calculator shows only the "hidden" costs: property tax, insurance, and maintenance. It does not include mortgage principal & interest, utilities, or HOA fees. Use it to budget beyond your monthly PITI.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quiz Section -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'hidden-costs', retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #e17055; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}" style="background: #2f2a24;">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test Your Knowledge: Hidden Costs</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. What does the "1% rule" refer to in homeownership?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Down payment should be at least 1% of the price</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Set aside 1% of home value annually for maintenance</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Property taxes are 1% of value</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Interest rates will rise 1% each year</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. Which of the following is typically escrowed into a mortgage payment?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Maintenance costs</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Property taxes</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Utilities</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Renovation budget</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. A home's assessed value for property taxes is often ___________ its market value.</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Less than</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Equal to</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Greater than</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Unrelated to</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. What is a common reason homeowners insurance costs vary by location?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">School district ratings</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Risk of natural disasters (floods, earthquakes, hurricanes)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Local property tax rates</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Distance to grocery stores</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. If you buy a $400,000 home and follow the 1% rule, how much should you budget for maintenance in the first year?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">$1,000</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">$2,000</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">$4,000</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">$40,000</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn" style="background-color: var(--real-estate-color);">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- Next Steps in Phase 2 -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Continue Phase 2: Risk Management</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'real-estate-market-risk' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i>
                    <h3>Market Risk & Cycles</h3>
                    <p>Understand booms and busts.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'vacancy-risk' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-door-open"></i>
                    <h3>Vacancy Risk</h3>
                    <p>Minimize empty units and lost income.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'real-state', slug: 'legal-liability' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-gavel"></i>
                    <h3>Legal & Liability Risks</h3>
                    <p>Insurance, LLCs, and protecting your assets.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
